  , issueCommentBody =
      "After some discussion with @mlucy here's what we came up with:\r\n\r\n1. Make `merge` be deep by default. Do not introduce a flag to control the deepness.\r\n2. Instead, introduce `r.val` and use it as follows:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nr.merge({a: {b1: {c: 1, d: 2 }}, b2: 1},\r\n        {a: {b1: {c: 2}}})\r\n     => {a: {b1: {c: 2, d: 2}}, b2: 1}\r\n\r\nr.merge({a: {b1: {c: 1, d: 2}}, b2: 1},\r\n        {a: {b1: r.val({ c: 2 })}})\r\n     => {a: {b1: {c: 2}}, b2: 1}\r\n```"
  , issueCommentId = 19236493
